rms (Google News, Medium)**: Personalizing news articles or blog posts for readers.\n","*   **Social Media (Facebook, TikTok)**: Recommending friends, groups, or content to keep users engaged.\n","\n","### ✨ Potential Enhancements:\n","\n","To make this recommendation system even more robust and powerful, here are some enhancements:\n","\n","*   **Hybrid Recommendation Systems**: Combine both content-based and collaborative filtering approaches to leverage their strengths and mitigate weaknesses. For instance, cold-start users could benefit from content-based recommendations, while established users could get more personalized collaborative filtering suggestions.\n","*   **Deep Learning Models**: Implement neural network-based recommendation systems (e.g., neural collaborative filtering, autoencoders) for more complex pattern recognition.\n","*   **Real-time Recommendations**: Integrate real-time user activity to provide instant and dynamic recommendations.\n","*   **Explainability**: Add features to explain *why* a certain movie was recommended, building user trust and understanding.\n","*   **A/B Testing**: Implement A/B testing frameworks to rigorously evaluate different recommendation algorithms and their impact on user engagement and satisfaction.\n","*   **User Interface (UI)**: Develop an interactive UI to allow users to input their preferences, view recommendations, and provide feedback.\n","*   **Feature Engineering**: Extract more rich features from movie data (e.g., sentiment from reviews, genre hierarchies, director/actor networks).\n","*   **Scalability**: For very large datasets, explore distributed computing frameworks like Spark for model training and prediction."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ============================================================\n","# STEP 1: INSTALL REQUIRED LIBRARIES (Only If Missing)\n","# ============================================================\n","\n","import sys\n","import subprocess\n","import importlib\n","\n